# T-5: approvals.json holds sensitive spend payloads (Amount, Recipient,
# Purpose) that approvalIssueBodyPublic redacts from the public GitHub
# issue. The file itself must stay local-only so the redaction is not
# undone by `git add`. Code (governance.js:loadApprovals) treats a
# missing file as { approvals: [] } so a fresh checkout works.
memory/approvals.json

# orbit-keygen output. Web3 Keystore v3 (encrypted, but the encryption is
# only as strong as the passphrase, and the file shape itself proves a key
# pair exists). Never commit. orbit-keygen claims it auto-adds this to
# .gitignore — adding here as belt + braces.
keys/
